CatDescriptText: Miss Grace Moore, 152 Third Ave., Aliquippa, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 28, 1957, pg.3 with question: "Do you think Pennsylvania's 'blue laws' against 'unnecessary' Sunday sales should be enforced?" answer reads: "I think they should be enforced because there should not be any sales on Sunday or on any legal holiday."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Grace Moore, wearing earrings and light colored tweed coat, holding dark gloves and handbag, standing in front of light colored marble pillar between store windows, one on left with stocking display and sign that reads "You are sure to please her with an Emma Jettick Gift Certificate", and one on right with female mannequin wearing dress
